<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,1599,2020]" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">
Radula 
<quantity box="[285,371,1599,1623]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="20" pageNumber="321" unit="mm" value="2.4">2.4 mm</quantity>
long, with 18 transverse rows of mature teeth, central teeth with wide blade, major lateral teeth with unidentate sharply pointed head.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="322" pageId="20" pageNumber="321" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,1599,2020]" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1671,1696]" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species belongs to the above mentioned 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1878" box="[896,1134,1671,1696]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="20" pageNumber="321" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="belknapi">
<emphasis box="[896,1134,1671,1696]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">Leptochiton belknapi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (
<bibRefCitation author="Sirenko" box="[1224,1380,1671,1696]" pageId="20" pageNumber="321" refId="ref17272" refString="Sirenko, V. I. (2015) Shallow and deep-sea chitons of the genus Leptoсhiton Gray, 1847 (Мollusca: Polyplacophora: Lepidopleurida) from Peruvian and Chilean waters. Zootaxa, 4033 (2), 151 - 202." type="journal article" year="2015">Sirenko 2015</bibRefCitation>
) and has strong similarities with several members of that group, namely: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saito" authorityYear="1997" box="[929,1116,1707,1732]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="20" pageNumber="321" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ater">
<emphasis box="[929,1116,1707,1732]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">Leptochiton ater</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="2016" box="[1132,1250,1708,1732]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="20" pageNumber="321" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="fijiensis">
<emphasis box="[1132,1250,1708,1732]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">L. fijiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saito" authorityYear="2011" box="[1266,1436,1707,1732]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="20" pageNumber="321" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="bergenhayni">
<emphasis box="[1266,1436,1707,1732]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">L. bergenhayni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thiele" authorityYear="1909" box="[199,338,1744,1767]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="20" pageNumber="321" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis box="[199,338,1744,1767]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">L. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Sirenko, 2018" authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="2018" box="[353,626,1743,1768]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="20" pageNumber="321" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="taiwanensis" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[353,626,1743,1768]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">Leptochiton taiwanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[634,697,1743,1768]" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[634,697,1743,1768]" pageId="20" pageNumber="321" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from these above mentioned species in having a tendency toward an arrangement of the granules in longitudinal rows in the jugal area of intermediate valves and in radial rows in other areas (vs. quincuncially, without this tendency to form rows in the other species). 
<taxonomicName authority="Sirenko, 2018" authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="2018" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="20" pageNumber="321" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="taiwanensis" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">Leptochiton taiwanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[290,354,1851,1876]" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[290,354,1851,1876]" pageId="20" pageNumber="321" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saito" authorityYear="1997" box="[562,637,1852,1875]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="20" pageNumber="321" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ater">
<emphasis box="[562,637,1852,1875]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">L. ater</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in features of radula, aesthete group and shape of tail valve, but differs from the latter in having wide dorsal girdle scales with 10–13 clear riblets (vs. narrow dorsal scales with 4–6 riblets in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saito" authorityYear="1997" box="[180,254,1924,1947]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="20" pageNumber="321" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ater">
<emphasis box="[180,254,1924,1947]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">L. ater</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,1599,2020]" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">
The new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saito" authorityYear="2011" box="[539,709,1959,1984]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="20" pageNumber="321" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="bergenhayni">
<emphasis box="[539,554,1960,1983]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[570,709,1959,1984]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">bergenhayni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having seven aesthetes in each granule (vs. 9 aesthetes in 
<taxonomicName class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="20" pageNumber="321" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="bergenhayeni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">L. bergenhayeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and posterior mucro (vs. central mucro in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saito" authorityYear="2011" box="[789,958,1995,2020]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="20" pageNumber="321" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="bergenhayni">
<emphasis box="[789,804,1996,2019]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[819,958,1995,2020]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">bergenhayni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,151,248]" box="[199,1436,151,176]" pageId="21" pageNumber="322">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="2018" box="[199,471,151,176]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="21" pageNumber="322" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="taiwanensis">
<emphasis box="[199,471,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="322">Leptochiton taiwanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="2016" box="[618,734,152,176]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="21" pageNumber="322" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="fijiensis">
<emphasis box="[618,734,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="322">L. fijiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thiele" authorityYear="1909" box="[788,926,153,176]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="21" pageNumber="322" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis box="[788,926,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="322">L. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having seven aesthetes in granule (vs. 11–
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,151,248]" pageId="21" pageNumber="322">
13 aesthetes in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="2016" box="[326,444,188,212]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="21" pageNumber="322" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="fijiensis">
<emphasis box="[326,444,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="322">L. fijiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<quantity box="[501,545,188,213]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="21" pageNumber="322" unit="in" value="5.0">5 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thiele" authorityYear="1909" box="[553,693,189,212]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="21" pageNumber="322" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis box="[553,693,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="322">L. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and 10–13 riblets on dorsal scales (vs. 6–7 riblets in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="2016" box="[1318,1436,188,212]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="21" pageNumber="322" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="fijiensis">
<emphasis box="[1318,1436,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="322">L. fijiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<quantity box="[198,241,223,248]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.778" pageId="21" pageNumber="322" unit="in" value="7.0">7 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thiele" authorityYear="1909" box="[248,386,225,248]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="21" pageNumber="322" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis box="[248,386,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="322">L. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
